summary: A Third Intrusive Thought Tony Stark had no problem telling Stephen Strange how he felt. “You’re annoying,” he groaned as they...
body:
A Third Intrusive Thought

Tony Stark had no problem telling Stephen Strange how he felt. “You’re annoying,” he groaned as they glided through space on the donut ship. “You turned my hair grey, leaving me with this mess” he sighed, hauling the freshly un-snapped Strange to his feet. “You’re driving me crazy!” he sighed as he carefully stitched the sorcerer up after a particularly rough battle. “I could never say no to you, Doc,” he teased, agreeing to repair the Sanctum’s heater. 

“I love you,” Tony Stark whispered, stretching on his toes to capture Stephen’s mouth with his own. 

Stephen Strange had every problem telling Tony Stark how he felt. “Douchebag,” he snapped, lacking the words to form a wittier response while smoldering eyes trapped him under their gaze. “You did well enough,” he offered breezily, still struggling to refrain from clinging to the man he’d spent millions of lifetimes with. “Your sanity was already lacking,” he sniffed, worried he’d crumble if he dared to apologize; if he dared acknowledge how Tony clearly worried for him. “A terrible character flaw,” he grumbled, cursing the traitorous smile that pulled at his lips as Tony chuckled behind him.

“A bit chalky,” Stephen Strange hummed, relishing the delightful taste of Tony Stark coating his tongue while his lover’s eyes shone bright.

After stopping a robbery you’re given sanctuary by the Avengers after exposing yourself as an unregistered mutant. After being on your own for years, you finally find the family you’ve always wanted. Tony was the cool older uncle. Natasha, the sister you never had. Steve was always there to give you advice and Sam was your partner in crime. But Bucky? Bucky was something else entirely.
